1
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:03,965
[TISSE]
Sorry to drop by so suddenly.

2
00:00:04,335 --> 00:00:06,257
Don't be. We're happy
to help with anything.

3
00:00:06,418 --> 00:00:07,879
Especially if it's urgent.

4
00:00:08,630 --> 00:00:10,922
Do you remember
Cardinal Ljubo?

5
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,634
Yeah.

6
00:00:12,724 --> 00:00:15,307
I think I saw him at the
Great Last Wall Fortress.

7
00:00:16,388 --> 00:00:19,811
I hear he's looking for the
former demon lord's airship.

8
00:01:55,701 --> 00:01:58,163
"Altra of the Water
dealt a crushing blow.

9
00:01:58,624 --> 00:02:01,457
Masked Knight Escarlata
defeats army general,

10
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:02,958
forcing a retreat."

11
00:02:03,589 --> 00:02:05,711
Makes me wonder who
this Knight is serving.

12
00:02:06,041 --> 00:02:07,633
Perhaps the Church?

13
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:09,135
A mercenary.

14
00:02:09,715 --> 00:02:10,716
Huh.

15
00:02:11,887 --> 00:02:14,180
Hey. About what Tisse said.

16
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,602
How the Cardinal wants
control of the airship.

17
00:02:17,473 --> 00:02:19,806
Is handing it over to
the Church the right call?

18
00:02:20,266 --> 00:02:22,228
It's better for them
to put it to use,

19
00:02:22,438 --> 00:02:24,440
than letting it rust
away in Zoltan.

20
00:02:24,981 --> 00:02:27,814
Until they give us a reason
to keep it out of their hands,

21
00:02:28,525 --> 00:02:29,526
I say we wait it out.

22
00:02:30,026 --> 00:02:31,027
Fair enough.

23
00:02:31,197 --> 00:02:32,569
Keeping Ruti safe.

24
00:02:32,739 --> 00:02:35,572
Ensuring no one finds her
is our top priority.

25
00:02:35,912 --> 00:02:37,704
♪

26
00:02:38,034 --> 00:02:39,706
No sign of any cold mold.

27
00:02:40,377 --> 00:02:41,378
[chuckling]

28
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,083
And the herbs are
growing nicely, too.

29
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:49,797
Yup. I've got your
advice to think for that.

30
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:53,721
Also, Tisse seems
to enjoy helping out.

31
00:02:53,891 --> 00:02:56,303
I do. I never thought
doing farm work

32
00:02:56,393 --> 00:02:58,305
with milady
would be this exciting!

33
00:02:59,056 --> 00:03:01,939
Might be worth thinking up
a sales plan moving forward.

34
00:03:02,690 --> 00:03:04,562
Let's start with my
apothecary shop.

35
00:03:04,942 --> 00:03:06,944
How about I purchase
your first harvest?

36
00:03:07,235 --> 00:03:08,196
All right.

37
00:03:08,276 --> 00:03:09,607
Next, we spread the word.

38
00:03:09,697 --> 00:03:11,489
Clinics and the
Merchants Guild.

39
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:14,742
Hmm. Traveling merchants
could make good customers.

40
00:03:15,783 --> 00:03:17,786
Does this mean you'll
help us with sales?

41
00:03:18,206 --> 00:03:19,367
Of course.

42
00:03:19,537 --> 00:03:21,539
I'm a member of the
Merchants Guild, you know.

43
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:23,922
And not to mention
your masterful guide

44
00:03:24,002 --> 00:03:25,373
to Zoltan easy living.

45
00:03:25,874 --> 00:03:27,626
My Master Big Brother.

46
00:03:28,627 --> 00:03:30,679
"Master Big Brother?" Hm?

47
00:03:33,342 --> 00:03:34,683
A lovely phrase.

48
00:03:34,843 --> 00:03:35,844
[chuckling]

49
00:03:37,386 --> 00:03:39,138
[grunting]

50
00:03:40,269 --> 00:03:41,270
[grunting]

51
00:03:47,486 --> 00:03:48,487
[growling]

52
00:03:50,239 --> 00:03:51,240
[grunting]

53
00:03:54,453 --> 00:03:55,705
[RED]
Looking good, Danan!

54
00:03:56,325 --> 00:03:57,617
Good enough!

55
00:03:57,787 --> 00:04:00,710
But, throw me in a fight and
I'll be back to full strength.

56
00:04:01,411 --> 00:04:03,713
Planning to leave Zoltan
once you're discharged?

57
00:04:04,164 --> 00:04:05,335
I'll miss seeing you.

58
00:04:05,505 --> 00:04:07,087
Tag along with me, Gideon!

59
00:04:07,377 --> 00:04:09,759
Together we can annihilate
the demon lord's army!

60
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:12,632
Pass.
My new life is here with Rit,

61
00:04:12,722 --> 00:04:14,264
running my apothecary shop.

62
00:04:14,514 --> 00:04:16,767
Ah, well. Suit yourself.

63
00:04:16,927 --> 00:04:19,179
Drinks, then? Before you go?

64
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:22,182
Why not? Although
there is one other thing

65
00:04:22,272 --> 00:04:24,274
that I'd like to do
before I bid you goodbye.

66
00:04:24,394 --> 00:04:25,355
What's that?

67
00:04:26,276 --> 00:04:27,277
A spar.

68
00:04:27,568 --> 00:04:28,569
♪

69
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,362
I want you to spar
with me, Gideon.

70
00:04:31,532 --> 00:04:32,533
♪

71
00:04:34,325 --> 00:04:35,906
[RIT]
And you said yes?

72
00:04:36,577 --> 00:04:37,578
[RED]
Yeah.

73
00:04:37,698 --> 00:04:40,201
He insisted he wanted
to before leaving Zoltan.

74
00:04:40,701 --> 00:04:43,624
I'll have to train like crazy.
It's been a while.

75
00:04:44,956 --> 00:04:46,047
Think you'll win?

76
00:04:46,377 --> 00:04:48,299
The truth? No, not a chance.

77
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,552
His Blessing is Martial Artist.

78
00:04:51,382 --> 00:04:54,345
It's pretty common.
But he adores his Blessing.

79
00:04:54,466 --> 00:04:56,177
And it favors him right back.

80
00:04:56,808 --> 00:04:57,769
Right.

81
00:04:57,849 --> 00:04:59,641
Now consider me as the Guide.

82
00:05:00,432 --> 00:05:03,395
I only have average skills
meant to protect a young Hero.

83
00:05:04,316 --> 00:05:06,398
Kinda obvious how
this spar will turn out.

84
00:05:07,649 --> 00:05:09,031
But you're still
going for it?

85
00:05:10,032 --> 00:05:11,033
I am.

86
00:05:11,323 --> 00:05:12,324
Huh.

87
00:05:13,035 --> 00:05:14,827
Then do you want
to spar with me?

88
00:05:15,577 --> 00:05:16,578
[gasps]

89
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,872
Come on, don't
give me that look.

90
00:05:19,952 --> 00:05:21,874
It's not like we've
ever sparred.

91
00:05:21,994 --> 00:05:22,955
If you're really worried,

92
00:05:23,045 --> 00:05:24,917
just cast Merciful
before the fight.

93
00:05:24,997 --> 00:05:27,460
Bet you're gonna use it
against Danan, anyway.

94
00:05:28,421 --> 00:05:29,422
True.

95
00:05:29,842 --> 00:05:32,345
The risk of scarring or
wounding my opponent is gone

96
00:05:32,425 --> 00:05:33,806
if the spell is in effect.

97
00:05:34,427 --> 00:05:36,639
Doesn't mean it
won't hurt all the same.

98
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,811
-Hm.
-Hmm?

99
00:05:41,354 --> 00:05:42,395
Sorry, I can't.

100
00:05:42,766 --> 00:05:43,767
[gasps]

101
00:05:45,398 --> 00:05:46,399
[grunting]

102
00:05:50,864 --> 00:05:51,865
[RED]
So rusty.

103
00:05:52,486 --> 00:05:55,118
At this rate, I'll only end
up letting Danan down.

104
00:05:56,079 --> 00:05:58,492
Here. Best to stay
hydrated while training.

105
00:05:58,912 --> 00:05:59,993
Appreciated.

106
00:06:00,414 --> 00:06:01,415
[YARANDRALA]
Red!

107
00:06:01,915 --> 00:06:02,916
Huh?

108
00:06:03,037 --> 00:06:05,920
Is it true you and Danan
are planning to spar?

109
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:07,922
Word gets around, I see.

110
00:06:08,592 --> 00:06:11,295
You should have told me sooner.
I would be thrilled to help.

111
00:06:11,926 --> 00:06:13,097
Please allow me
to train you

112
00:06:13,177 --> 00:06:15,389
and help you brush up on
your combat skills.

113
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,552
That's very kind
of you to offer,

114
00:06:17,682 --> 00:06:19,474
but I thought you
were a spirit mage.

115
00:06:20,014 --> 00:06:22,607
Well, aside from
my magecraft,

116
00:06:22,687 --> 00:06:24,859
I also founded the
Lotus-Style Staff Technique.

117
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:28,773
You're the founder? That style
is super famous everywhere!

118
00:06:28,983 --> 00:06:30,155
And get this.

119
00:06:30,365 --> 00:06:32,067
You know that book
detailing various

120
00:06:32,157 --> 00:06:33,658
regions' military tactics?

121
00:06:33,868 --> 00:06:37,032
The famous "One Hundred
Strategies, the Beauty of War?"

122
00:06:37,372 --> 00:06:39,785
Authored by none
other than Yorondrala!

123
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:40,876
That's so amazing!

124
00:06:41,707 --> 00:06:44,169
Well, sitting on my hands
as the years marched on

125
00:06:44,249 --> 00:06:45,500
felt wasteful.

126
00:06:45,751 --> 00:06:47,883
But back to more
pressing matters, you two.

127
00:06:48,253 --> 00:06:50,045
What I think you
need right now, Red,

128
00:06:50,135 --> 00:06:52,678
is to dig deep and
sharpen that mind of yours.

129
00:06:53,008 --> 00:06:56,011
Rediscovering and honing your
past skills will not be easy.

130
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:58,594
This well of strength from
which you pull must be

131
00:06:58,684 --> 00:07:00,976
different than what you've
relied upon in the past!

132
00:07:01,057 --> 00:07:02,268
That makes sense.

133
00:07:02,518 --> 00:07:05,151
The me from before
Zoltan is long gone now.

134
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:07,693
Which means I'll
have to train in a way

135
00:07:07,773 --> 00:07:09,405
that plays to Red's strengths.

136
00:07:09,816 --> 00:07:11,277
Now that's the spirit!

137
00:07:11,357 --> 00:07:13,780
Then we should begin
your training camp at once!

138
00:07:13,990 --> 00:07:16,913
- Training camp? - You grab
your bags too, dear Red!

139
00:07:17,534 --> 00:07:20,617
♪

140
00:07:22,038 --> 00:07:23,330
Did I keep you waiting?

141
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,752
Not at all.
I just got here.

142
00:07:26,373 --> 00:07:27,374
[chuckles]

143
00:07:27,504 --> 00:07:29,005
The two of you
were just waiting to

144
00:07:29,086 --> 00:07:30,967
play out that tired
cliche, weren't you?

145
00:07:31,508 --> 00:07:33,931
Go on. Just admit it.
Don't be shy.

146
00:07:34,381 --> 00:07:37,684
Admit what?
Ruti just cares about me!

147
00:07:38,055 --> 00:07:39,476
Did I keep you waiting?

148
00:07:39,556 --> 00:07:41,348
Not at all.
I just got here.

149
00:07:41,438 --> 00:07:44,692
-Did I keep you waiting?
-Not at all. I just got here.

150
00:07:44,772 --> 00:07:45,943
Did I keep you wait--

151
00:07:46,023 --> 00:07:47,024
Hate to interrupt,

152
00:07:47,144 --> 00:07:50,027
but are you sure you can handle
training alongside m'lady?

153
00:07:50,608 --> 00:07:53,030
You're talking to the guy
who taught Ruti swordplay.

154
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:56,073
Of course a teacher can keep
up with his favorite student.

155
00:07:56,494 --> 00:07:58,906
Looking forward to
learning with you, big brother.

156
00:07:59,827 --> 00:08:01,910
[DANAN] Training camps test the
mettle of one's character.

157
00:08:02,871 --> 00:08:05,083
-It's the highest form of play.
-Huh?

158
00:08:05,163 --> 00:08:07,916
[RED] Danan!
Discharged already?

159
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:10,128
Yeah. No way
I'm gonna sit back

160
00:08:10,218 --> 00:08:11,670
while you guys
have all the fun.

161
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:14,302
Count me in on
the camping trip.

162
00:08:14,723 --> 00:08:16,014
Figured as much.

163
00:08:16,384 --> 00:08:17,556
You ready to head out?

164
00:08:18,266 --> 00:08:19,267
All set.

165
00:08:20,228 --> 00:08:21,229
[water flowing]

166
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:25,774
♪

167
00:08:26,145 --> 00:08:28,567
Right, tense her up so that
just leaves the firewood.

168
00:08:29,108 --> 00:08:30,109
[TISSE]
Done.

169
00:08:34,653 --> 00:08:35,654
[panting]

170
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:42,832
Come now!
Be mindful of the ecosystem!

171
00:08:44,454 --> 00:08:47,086
Break over!
Time for another firewood run!

172
00:08:47,627 --> 00:08:48,628
He's not listening.

173
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,551
[RIT] First meal
of training camp

174
00:08:51,631 --> 00:08:53,553
is Red's custom
training lunch!

175
00:08:55,095 --> 00:08:56,096
[ALL gasping]

176
00:08:57,427 --> 00:08:58,888
There's just one problem.

177
00:08:58,969 --> 00:09:00,891
I don't think we have
enough for Danan.

178
00:09:01,431 --> 00:09:02,432
Have mine instead.

179
00:09:02,772 --> 00:09:04,815
Thanks, but I'm strong
enough to go without.

180
00:09:06,226 --> 00:09:07,317
Please take it.

181
00:09:07,397 --> 00:09:09,529
Even though hunger
is a new feeling for me,

182
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:10,941
I'd rather you have it.

183
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:13,824
Feel free to take
half of mine, m'lady.

184
00:09:14,284 --> 00:09:16,286
Let me offer you
half of mine as well.

185
00:09:21,121 --> 00:09:23,584
Half and half makes
one whole meal.

186
00:09:24,245 --> 00:09:25,746
That doesn't seem fair.

187
00:09:26,457 --> 00:09:28,379
Wait, wait. Try this.

188
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,382
[RED] Now we all grab
whatever we want.

189
00:09:31,712 --> 00:09:32,713
[RUTI] Smart idea.

190
00:09:33,464 --> 00:09:34,806
Sorry for the trouble.

191
00:09:34,886 --> 00:09:36,387
But if you guys really insist,

192
00:09:36,597 --> 00:09:38,810
thanks for the meal.
Don't mind if I do.

193
00:09:38,970 --> 00:09:39,971
[chomps]

194
00:09:42,013 --> 00:09:43,014
[chuckling]

195
00:09:45,437 --> 00:09:46,438
Say something.

196
00:09:51,153 --> 00:09:52,654
It's been quite
a while since the old

197
00:09:52,734 --> 00:09:54,696
gang got together
like this, hasn't it?

198
00:09:54,946 --> 00:09:57,779
Theodora's missing.
And we can't forget Ares.

199
00:09:59,031 --> 00:10:00,032
Hm.

200
00:10:01,163 --> 00:10:02,164
[DANAN]
That's true.

201
00:10:04,206 --> 00:10:05,838
Oh right, I forgot to ask you.

202
00:10:06,208 --> 00:10:07,960
Did you happen to
look at the newspaper?

203
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,504
Some hotshot mercenary
defeated Astra of the Water.

204
00:10:12,044 --> 00:10:14,347
You mean the
Masked Knight, Escarlata?

205
00:10:14,927 --> 00:10:16,639
That's gotta be Theodora.

206
00:10:16,929 --> 00:10:19,101
Think, is there any other
knight on this continent

207
00:10:19,182 --> 00:10:21,604
who can beat a general
of such high caliber?

208
00:10:22,225 --> 00:10:23,396
And don't forget,

209
00:10:23,476 --> 00:10:25,979
where she is, her right-hand
man's not far behind.

210
00:10:26,309 --> 00:10:28,231
The knight with the
prosthetic right arm.

211
00:10:28,982 --> 00:10:30,904
Can't be anyone
else but Albert.

212
00:10:31,564 --> 00:10:32,906
[DANAN]
Oh him.

213
00:10:33,196 --> 00:10:34,868
Still gotta
thank him for saving me.

214
00:10:35,488 --> 00:10:36,910
After leaving Zoltan,

215
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:39,453
I plan to meet up with
Theodora first thing.

216
00:10:39,783 --> 00:10:41,875
If she wants to finish
off the Water General

217
00:10:41,955 --> 00:10:43,997
for good then, I'll
happily join her.

218
00:10:44,578 --> 00:10:45,579
Hm?

219
00:10:46,129 --> 00:10:49,883
In case you were unaware, I've
yet to sample the duck saute.

220
00:10:50,174 --> 00:10:51,175
Gimme that.

221
00:10:51,715 --> 00:10:52,716
[YARANDRALA]
Honestly, Danan!

222
00:10:53,047 --> 00:10:54,048
-[grunts]
-[clanking]

223
00:10:54,338 --> 00:10:55,339
[gasps]

224
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:57,641
[YARANDRALA, DANAN]
Ruti!

225
00:11:00,434 --> 00:11:02,096
[DANAN]
Okay, time to fight.

226
00:11:02,266 --> 00:11:05,189
♪

227
00:11:07,021 --> 00:11:09,153
-Should we train too?
-Indeed.

228
00:11:09,444 --> 00:11:11,356
There's something
else I want to do. Bye.

229
00:11:11,906 --> 00:11:12,907
Wait for me.

230
00:11:13,107 --> 00:11:15,109
♪

231
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,351
[water gushing]

232
00:11:59,245 --> 00:12:01,157
I still feel exactly the same.

233
00:12:02,579 --> 00:12:03,580
That's weird.

234
00:12:03,710 --> 00:12:06,873
Why is it weird? I didn't
expect anything different.

235
00:12:07,754 --> 00:12:08,875
You didn't?

236
00:12:08,965 --> 00:12:11,378
Now I want to know
what you were expecting.

237
00:12:11,878 --> 00:12:13,009
Wait.

238
00:12:13,129 --> 00:12:14,551
Something smells nice.

239
00:12:14,721 --> 00:12:16,633
Rit and Yarandrala's cooking,
maybe?

240
00:12:16,883 --> 00:12:18,845
I think they're on
dinner duty tonight.

241
00:12:19,806 --> 00:12:20,847
Should be good.

242
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:24,431
[sighs]

243
00:12:25,142 --> 00:12:27,274
Your swordplay
makes your foe visible.

244
00:12:27,684 --> 00:12:28,686
My foe?

245
00:12:28,896 --> 00:12:30,648
That's right.
Each of your moves

246
00:12:30,738 --> 00:12:32,900
tells me what kind of
enemy you're cutting down.

247
00:12:34,241 --> 00:12:36,494
I do picture them, I guess.

248
00:12:37,364 --> 00:12:39,697
Humans, and
elves, and monsters,

249
00:12:40,077 --> 00:12:42,870
demons, all walks
of life fighting you.

250
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,792
I see them crystal clear.

251
00:12:45,203 --> 00:12:48,086
Goes to show you how adaptable
your tactics are in combat.

252
00:12:48,376 --> 00:12:50,418
Sparring with you
is all the fire I need.

253
00:12:51,089 --> 00:12:52,090
Likewise.

254
00:12:53,051 --> 00:12:54,052
♪

255
00:13:04,813 --> 00:13:05,814
[water rushing]

256
00:13:07,686 --> 00:13:09,688
[RIT] Hey you.
Need me to wash your back?

257
00:13:09,778 --> 00:13:10,779
Huh?

258
00:13:16,075 --> 00:13:18,447
Yes, please.
If you wouldn't mind.

259
00:13:23,292 --> 00:13:24,293
Hm.

260
00:13:25,414 --> 00:13:27,586
So training with
Danan today went well.

261
00:13:28,207 --> 00:13:29,999
Really drove home
how strong he is.

262
00:13:30,209 --> 00:13:31,881
Wouldn't be too far
off the mark to call him

263
00:13:31,961 --> 00:13:34,634
the strongest human.
After Ruti, of course.

264
00:13:34,884 --> 00:13:36,806
He is pretty impressive,
isn't he?

265
00:13:37,307 --> 00:13:39,218
This isn't just another spar.

266
00:13:39,349 --> 00:13:41,060
It's not for fun
or a deathmatch.

267
00:13:41,601 --> 00:13:43,763
Winning or losing
isn't the point, either.

268
00:13:44,314 --> 00:13:45,645
Then what is the point?

269
00:13:46,186 --> 00:13:48,108
Danan's a warrior to the core.

270
00:13:48,478 --> 00:13:50,230
Quiet life couldn't
be more different.

271
00:13:51,111 --> 00:13:52,903
But there's strength
in easy living,

272
00:13:53,023 --> 00:13:55,075
and I'll show him
that through our spar.

273
00:13:55,575 --> 00:13:58,198
You two have been through
a lot together as friends.

274
00:13:58,659 --> 00:14:00,450
I hope he understands.

275
00:14:01,532 --> 00:14:02,533
Me too.

276
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:14,045
Fighters, keep still
while I cast Merciful.

277
00:14:16,717 --> 00:14:18,849
This inhibits
wounds, but be aware

278
00:14:18,930 --> 00:14:21,012
this spell does not
prevent pain, yes?

279
00:14:25,687 --> 00:14:27,559
No hard feelings, okay, guys?

280
00:14:30,021 --> 00:14:30,942
Begin!

281
00:14:31,022 --> 00:14:32,193
♪

282
00:14:32,694 --> 00:14:33,695
[grunts]

283
00:14:36,318 --> 00:14:38,570
Martial art,
rampaging kick!

284
00:14:39,451 --> 00:14:40,412
[grunts]

285
00:14:42,704 --> 00:14:45,497
♪

286
00:14:46,628 --> 00:14:47,629
Crap!

287
00:14:49,251 --> 00:14:50,252
[slicing]

288
00:14:50,582 --> 00:14:51,583
[grunting]

289
00:14:54,677 --> 00:14:55,678
[grunts]

290
00:14:55,758 --> 00:14:56,759
-[slicing]
-[thuds]

291
00:14:59,842 --> 00:15:01,934
Martial art, pulverizing punch!

292
00:15:03,646 --> 00:15:04,647
[grunts]

293
00:15:10,313 --> 00:15:12,445
It really is just
a normal sword.

294
00:15:13,446 --> 00:15:15,738
And I'm supposed to be
the stronger one between us.

295
00:15:16,359 --> 00:15:18,111
But you saw through
every one of my moves,

296
00:15:18,201 --> 00:15:20,533
and even made contact
with this simple blade.

297
00:15:22,245 --> 00:15:23,246
[chuckling]

298
00:15:23,867 --> 00:15:26,119
You know what,
Gideon? You're a fun.

299
00:15:26,329 --> 00:15:28,371
There's never a dull
moment when you're around.

300
00:15:28,752 --> 00:15:30,504
You have figured out
how to win, though.

301
00:15:30,794 --> 00:15:31,925
I can see it in your eyes.

302
00:15:32,255 --> 00:15:33,256
Nice catch.

303
00:15:33,797 --> 00:15:36,220
I'm itching to see how
long you can keep this up.

304
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:38,302
You're managing to
block every hit from me

305
00:15:38,382 --> 00:15:40,384
because you're
predicting them, aren't you?

306
00:15:40,764 --> 00:15:43,978
Yeah, of course I am.
How else will I defend myself?

307
00:15:44,478 --> 00:15:46,811
So all I gotta do to win
is use moves I wouldn't

308
00:15:46,891 --> 00:15:48,192
normally rely on.

309
00:15:48,642 --> 00:15:50,354
Holding back some is the key.

310
00:15:50,775 --> 00:15:53,858
"Holding back". Huh.
That's your strategy?

311
00:15:54,528 --> 00:15:56,150
The hell do you think I am?

312
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,953
We're sparring, so I'm
not swinging to kill you.

313
00:15:59,363 --> 00:16:01,115
Just because I'm
not trying to kill you

314
00:16:01,205 --> 00:16:03,157
doesn't mean that I won't fight

315
00:16:03,248 --> 00:16:04,829
at my absolute peak!

316
00:16:04,959 --> 00:16:06,291
I expect nothing less!

317
00:16:06,411 --> 00:16:07,412
-[grunts]
-[clang]

318
00:16:07,832 --> 00:16:09,464
Give it your all, Gideon!

319
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:12,087
So those eyes of yours
can see right through me

320
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:13,258
at my full strength?

321
00:16:13,508 --> 00:16:15,670
Guess that means I'll
have to transcend my limits

322
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,262
and go above and beyond!

323
00:16:17,883 --> 00:16:19,174
Then bring it!

324
00:16:19,344 --> 00:16:21,056
I'll meet you blow for blow!

325
00:16:21,386 --> 00:16:23,348
And prove what I've
gained from this life!

326
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:25,681
[grunts]

327
00:16:26,812 --> 00:16:27,813
[grunts]

328
00:16:28,814 --> 00:16:29,895
Ready, Gideon?

329
00:16:30,736 --> 00:16:31,737
Ready, Danan!

330
00:16:32,027 --> 00:16:35,361
♪

331
00:16:36,942 --> 00:16:37,943
[grunts]

332
00:16:39,195 --> 00:16:42,538
Ow. Stupid me
charging into a direct hit.

333
00:16:43,829 --> 00:16:46,502
I'd be a goner if it wasn't
for Yarandrala's spell.

334
00:16:46,702 --> 00:16:47,704
[chuckling]

335
00:16:48,544 --> 00:16:51,047
I knew all along you were
a force to be reckoned with.

336
00:16:51,377 --> 00:16:53,339
I just hope I didn't
disappoint you.

337
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:55,171
Not even close.

338
00:16:55,672 --> 00:16:58,094
Can't say I totally
get this chill life thing.

339
00:16:59,015 --> 00:17:01,848
So I thought fighting you might
help me wrap my head around it.

340
00:17:02,429 --> 00:17:05,061
Fighting's the only language
I speak, and it's how I think.

341
00:17:05,222 --> 00:17:08,185
And? Learn anything
about my lifestyle?

342
00:17:08,685 --> 00:17:09,977
Not one thing.

343
00:17:10,277 --> 00:17:11,939
But you know what, Gideon?

344
00:17:12,229 --> 00:17:13,230
I mean, Red.

345
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:15,442
It is subtle, but
your swordplay

346
00:17:15,532 --> 00:17:17,324
has a raw and
formidable strength.

347
00:17:17,985 --> 00:17:20,197
You're the same tough
guy I've come to respect

348
00:17:20,287 --> 00:17:22,239
who's just chosen a
different path to walk.

349
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,743
To your damnedest to
live happily ever after.

350
00:17:26,243 --> 00:17:27,995
Easy living is strength, too.

351
00:17:28,546 --> 00:17:29,997
Sure will. Thanks.

352
00:17:30,418 --> 00:17:33,301
As for me, the thrill of
the battle is why I fight.

353
00:17:33,711 --> 00:17:35,883
My desire is my
source of pride.

354
00:17:36,214 --> 00:17:37,425
Your strength.

355
00:17:37,505 --> 00:17:39,717
It's what I respect
most about you, Danan.

356
00:17:39,887 --> 00:17:41,139
Relentless and free.

357
00:17:41,679 --> 00:17:42,680
[chuckling]

358
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:46,144
All right.
It's my turn next, Danan.

359
00:17:46,394 --> 00:17:47,265
[gasps]

360
00:17:47,355 --> 00:17:51,019
Seriously? I get to spar with
the world's strongest hero?

361
00:17:51,439 --> 00:17:53,151
Not even
my wildest dreams did I--

362
00:17:53,231 --> 00:17:54,232
-[thuds]
-[grunts]

363
00:17:56,945 --> 00:18:00,579
Come on! There's gotta be some
way I can still pull a wind.

364
00:18:00,869 --> 00:18:01,870
[laughing]

365
00:18:04,373 --> 00:18:06,205
I feel so bad for him.

366
00:18:06,535 --> 00:18:07,536
Sorry.

367
00:18:09,498 --> 00:18:10,499
♪

368
00:18:15,965 --> 00:18:17,717
Long time no see, Albert.

369
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:19,348
It's been a while.

370
00:18:19,719 --> 00:18:21,100
Are you back for good?

371
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,972
Talk about a nice surprise.

372
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:24,854
I arrived here today.

373
00:18:25,355 --> 00:18:28,228
Mister Red and Miss Rit, I'm
glad to see that you're well.

374
00:18:28,518 --> 00:18:31,191
Did I hear "Mister"?
That's a first.

375
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:32,612
Strange, I know.

376
00:18:32,732 --> 00:18:35,235
Please, no reminders
of the man I once was.

377
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:37,277
Did Theodora come with you?

378
00:18:37,737 --> 00:18:39,529
No, she's not here in Zoltan.

379
00:18:40,030 --> 00:18:41,031
I came alone.

380
00:18:41,201 --> 00:18:43,203
She's taken the
name of Escarlotta.

381
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:46,326
I have a message from her,
and an urgent one at that.

382
00:18:46,997 --> 00:18:47,998
What message?

383
00:18:49,039 --> 00:18:51,542
"Take heed that a new
Hero has appeared.

384
00:18:52,042 --> 00:18:54,795
[ALBERT]
His name is Van of Flamberge.

385
00:18:55,716 --> 00:18:57,428
He may make his way to Zoltan,

386
00:18:57,548 --> 00:19:00,341
in order to take the former
demon lord's airship."

387
00:19:06,807 --> 00:19:08,349
-[door creaks open]
-[indistinct chatter]

388
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:10,021
[VAN]
Such commotion.

389
00:19:10,231 --> 00:19:11,903
[LAVENDER]
Looks lively, doesn't it?

390
00:19:13,815 --> 00:19:16,698
Lavender, stay close to me.
Out of danger.

391
00:19:16,988 --> 00:19:19,280
Will you keep me safe from
all the scary people?

392
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:21,783
Indeed.
No harm will come to you.

393
00:19:22,283 --> 00:19:23,495
Goodness me!

394
00:19:23,575 --> 00:19:26,458
When you say things like that,
I'd do anything for you!

395
00:19:27,209 --> 00:19:28,210
[crashing]

396
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:31,423
Hey! Got something
funny to share with the bar?

397
00:19:31,543 --> 00:19:33,005
You're giving me a good reason

398
00:19:33,085 --> 00:19:35,047
to claim self-defense
here, pal!

399
00:19:35,297 --> 00:19:36,298
[grunting]

400
00:19:37,589 --> 00:19:39,181
Sorry, but you had it coming!

401
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:41,263
Need to keep my
Blessing from running wild,

402
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:43,686
or else the urges
just get worse!

403
00:19:43,936 --> 00:19:44,937
[laughing]

404
00:19:46,098 --> 00:19:48,390
Do any of his buddies
want to volunteer too?

405
00:19:48,731 --> 00:19:50,563
Step right up,
don't be shy now.

406
00:19:50,693 --> 00:19:52,895
You do want to avenge your
dead friend here, don't you?

407
00:19:52,985 --> 00:19:54,947
[MALE RUFFIAN 205B]
Come on, hurry up and fight me!

408
00:19:55,988 --> 00:19:57,240
A wrongdoer blessing.

409
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,611
[MALE RUFFIAN 205B]
Give you your life!

410
00:19:58,781 --> 00:19:59,782
[slicing]

411
00:20:02,405 --> 00:20:03,406
[thuds]

412
00:20:07,290 --> 00:20:08,501
Be gone now, evil.

413
00:20:14,007 --> 00:20:15,629
What is going on over here?

414
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:18,552
Nothing. Van just struck down
a very strange fellow.

415
00:20:18,762 --> 00:20:22,516
Yes. This one murdered another
patron, so I killed him.

416
00:20:23,477 --> 00:20:24,888
Start from the beginning, Van.

417
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:26,890
First, a reason for the fight.

418
00:20:27,231 --> 00:20:30,184
Reason? Does a reason matter
in the grand scheme of things?

419
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:33,437
It'll shed light on your
motivation to kill outright.

420
00:20:33,988 --> 00:20:35,569
You could have easily
captured him alive

421
00:20:35,649 --> 00:20:37,071
before resorting to murder.

422
00:20:37,942 --> 00:20:40,444
An interrogation
would be beneficial here.

423
00:20:40,865 --> 00:20:42,657
What a curious statement.

424
00:20:43,327 --> 00:20:45,620
You do realize he had
a wrongdoer blessing?

425
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,332
That doesn't deny
one's humanity.

426
00:20:48,703 --> 00:20:51,586
People's lives involve
more than a blessing's urges.

427
00:20:52,046 --> 00:20:54,008
Everyone has
their own free will.

428
00:20:54,339 --> 00:20:55,920
You must never forget that.

429
00:20:56,631 --> 00:20:58,713
You seem to
misunderstand the situation.

430
00:20:59,134 --> 00:21:00,885
-Do I?
-Let me elaborate.

431
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:04,139
By no means am I implying that
your statements are incorrect.

432
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:07,522
I felt no hatred for that
beheaded corpse,

433
00:21:07,723 --> 00:21:10,686
nor was preventing further
casualties here my priority.

434
00:21:11,276 --> 00:21:12,898
The blade of the
hero is not meant

435
00:21:12,978 --> 00:21:14,480
to satisfy personal ambition.

436
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:16,361
Above all else, Esta,

437
00:21:16,572 --> 00:21:18,734
my battles are
offerings to the Almighty.

438
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:20,736
But why'd you kill him, Van?

439
00:21:21,327 --> 00:21:22,738
[VAN] People with the
Wrongdoer Blessing

440
00:21:22,828 --> 00:21:25,161
exist solely to be
executed by another.

441
00:21:25,911 --> 00:21:27,623
His death by my
blade fulfilled the

442
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:29,455
role he was put
on this soil for.

443
00:21:30,416 --> 00:21:32,668
In truth, I do feel stronger.

444
00:21:32,839 --> 00:21:35,211
A strength achieved
in exchange for his life.

445
00:21:36,843 --> 00:21:39,636
I offer love and
blessings to his sacrifice.

446
00:21:39,846 --> 00:21:42,509
My blessing, which has
grown at the cost of his life,

447
00:21:42,809 --> 00:21:44,971
will surely save
the world one day.

448
00:21:45,261 --> 00:21:46,893
Do you hear yourself?

449
00:21:47,013 --> 00:21:48,565
Words of a true hero.

450
00:21:49,316 --> 00:21:50,477
Oh, not yet.

451
00:21:50,937 --> 00:21:52,859
Even now, I stand
here before my party,

452
00:21:52,939 --> 00:21:55,232
untested by the
demon lord's forces.

453
00:21:55,822 --> 00:21:57,694
I am a hero in name only.

454
00:21:58,075 --> 00:22:00,327
Hero Ruti's faith runs
deeper than mine.

455
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:04,992
Are we finished here?

456
00:22:05,082 --> 00:22:07,785
If so, we should
head to Zoltan at once.

